                            <outline text="Definitions of a Bayesian Nash Equilibrium (BNE)">
<outline text="Non-bayesian game: strategy profile is a NE if every strategy in that profile is a best response to every other strategy"/>
<outline text="Bayesian Games: Players maximise their expected payoffs">
    <outline text="Pooling Equilibrium if the first player sends the same signal, regardless of his type (A or NA)"/>
    <outline text="Separating Equilibrium if the first player sends different signals, depending on his types (A or NA)"/>
</outline>
                            </outline>
                            <outline text="Results: Give conditions under which a pure strategy BNE exists for the signalling game"/>
