            <outline text="Mobile Secret Sharing Architectures #h1">
                <outline text="In this section, we discuss secret sharing architectures in a mobile setting. Depending on which stage of the secret sharing protocol is implemented on the mobile device, we differentiate between mobile dealer, mobile shareholder and mobile combiner, or a combination of these in a hybrid architecture. "/>
                <outline text="__Mobile Dealer__ -- in this architecture, the sensitive information (the secret) is on the mobile device at the time when the shares are created. Typical examples are mobile users who wish to protect their application data, present on their device. "/>
                <outline text="__Mobile Shareholders__ -- mobile cloud"/>
                <outline text="__Mobile Combiner__ -- Threshold operations"/>
                <outline text="__Hybrid__ -- ">
                    <outline text="Several Mobile Components"/>
                </outline>
            </outline>
