            <outline text="Evaluation #h1">
                <outline text="The key aim of the evaluation described in this section is a systematic performance study of secret sharing combiner algorithms, based on comparing the computational time for both an implemented desktop application and a mobile testbed."/>
                <outline text="We compare the combining of shares in the context of Shamir $$(t,n)$$ threshold secret sharing, using standard Lagrange interpolation, improved Lagrange and Barycentric approach."/>
                <outline text="Implementation #h2 ">
                    <outline text="All implementation was done in Java 7 as a generic test library for use in both the Desktop and Mobile code."/>
                    <outline text="The desktop implementation was tested on a Intel Core i7 4790 @ 3.60GHz PC with  16GB memory, and a 1GB allocated memory for the JVM.">
                        <outline text="[Dual-Channel DDR3 @ 798MHz ]"/>
                        <outline text="[CPU Haswell 22nm Technology]"/>
                    </outline>
                    <outline text="The mobile app was tested on a Samsung Galaxy tab (Tab S2 with a Snapdragon 652 @ 1.8 GHz and 3GB memory with same allocated memory for JVM as the desktop environment.">
                        <outline text="[DDR3 @ 825MHz]"/>
                        <outline text="[CPU 28 nm HPm]"/>
